						<summary>

						<p>A much damaged inscription contains two verses in praise of a Pāṇḍya king [Vaḻuti] who had the surname Vāḷāl-vaḻi-tiṟandāṉ. A second set of two verses evidently in praise of the same king, who is here called Kūḍalūr Kōmāṉ mentions the damming of the sea with his sword.</p>						

						</summary>
